$interpreted: Bounty Hunter: Human, you're dead meat!
Bounty Hunter: Damn!! Where'd he go? I definitely saw him heading in this direction...
Bounty Hunter: Search here!
Bounty Hunter: We've got to get this guy. He killed countless comrades. I want their blood to be paid for with blood!
Nanny: *sigh*...I'm not sure how many of them will hatch smoothly...
Religious Cleric: They are orphans of the battlefield. Even if they hatch successfully, countless difficulties lie ahead.
Religious Cleric: Whether they live or die depends on the mercy of the Snake God. All we can do is accept the fate that he has bestowed upon us.
Nanny: This is true...
Lazer: It's easy to speak of that which does not concern you.
Lazer: And if the Snake God abandons them, which one of you will take responsibility?
Religious Cleric: A human!?....Who-Who are you?
Lazer: I'm here to help.
Lazer: Kill me, or I'll kill you all.
Nanny: ...He's-He's crazy!
Lazer: Time to die!
Lazer: Death is better than this! Life is nothing more than suffering!
Lazer: It would be better to have never been born.
Lazer: When you grow up, you'll be forced onto the battlefield, frightened and in pain.
Lazer: You will be used...and betrayed.
Lazer: You'll become embittered, lose all self-respect, and yearn for liberation.
Lazer: If you don't die, you'll become a respected warrior and all you'll know is how to annihilate the enemy...even those who have yet to be born...
Little Lizard: *gurgle*......hehe!
Lazer: ......
Little Lizard: ...meh...mee!
Lazer: ......
Lazer: Get off!
Lazer: Don't touch me! Today is the day you die!
Little Lizard: ...waaahh...waaaah! WAH!
Lazer: Damn it! Get off me!
Little Lizard: Waaaaah!
Lazer: ...Sounded like something snapped...
Lazer: Don't come crawling to me!
Little Lizard: Waaah...waaah!
Lazer: Quit your crying, you little baby!
Lazer: You're finger's been broken! Painful, isn't it!? Now you see that life is worse than death. Why would you want——
Little Lizard: ...waaah...waah...
Lazer: Why would you want——
Lazer: ......
Lazer: ......
Lazer: Why would you want to...
Little Lizard: ...waah...
Lazer: Why would you want to live? Even your country is willing to throw you to the wolves...it's too...painful...
Lazer: ...Wh-Why...why...
Little Lizard: ...waah...waah...
Lazer: ......Thank you, child.
